The paper presents a heuristic algorithm for the Steiner Problem in Graphs, which is a well-studied problem in computer science. The algorithm uses multistart and elite solution combination techniques, which are commonly used in optimization and search algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a fast implementation of a dual ascent algorithm, which is a well-known optimization technique in operations research (cs.RO). The problem involves finding the minimum cost tree that spans a set of given vertices, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance on various graph classes, which is a common practice in machine learning and optimization research (cs.LG).
